primary_outcome.description:
The severity of COVID-19 related respiratory disease is assessed on the following seven-point ordinal scale:
not hospitalized with resumption of normal activities;
not hospitalized, but unable to resume normal activities;
hospitalized, not requiring supplemental oxygen;
hospitalized, requiring supplemental oxygen;
hospitalized, requiring nasal high-flow oxygen therapy, non-invasive mechanical ventilation, or both;
hospitalized, requiring Extracorporeal Membrane Oxygenation (ECMO), invasive mechanical ventilation, or both, and;
death. For the current study the primary efficacy outcome measure will be the proportion of patients with clinical improvement at 28 days of follow-up, defined as an improvement of two points on the seven-point ordinal scale.
